---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Customer Signal Engine · Mollie Cox"
  description="Building a customer engagement program that turned ad hoc feedback into a repeatable VOC loop during a major product transformation."
>
  <!-- ============================== -->
  <!-- HERO -->
  <!-- ============================== -->
  <section class="case-hero-dark">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-20 md:py-28 relative z-10">
      <a
        href="/#work"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cream/60 hover:text-orange transition-colors mb-16"
      >
        ← All work
      </a>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-12 items-start">

        <!-- Text column -->
        <div class="md:col-span-7">
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-6">Branch · 2025 to 2026</p>

          <h1 class="font-display text-display-lg text-cream leading-[0.95] tracking-tight">
            Building a customer signal engine<span class="brand-period">.</span>
          </h1>

          <p class="mt-10 text-xl text-cream/80 leading-relaxed max-w-[48ch]">
            A structured customer engagement program designed to deepen product
            feedback loops, strengthen trust, and support adoption during a major
            product transformation. EMEA pilot, North America rollout, formalized as
            part of the broader Product Experience strategy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Artifact column: concentric rings with bold center -->
        <div class="md:col-span-5 flex justify-center md:justify-end items-start mt-8 md:mt-0">
          <div class="case-hero-artifact w-full max-w-sm md:max-w-none">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 480 440" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Concentric rings expanding outward from a prominent central anchor, with customer nodes at varying distances representing degrees of access and trust">

              <!-- Subtle grid backdrop -->
              <g opacity="0.06">
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="80" y1="20" x2="80" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="160" y1="20" x2="160" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="240" y1="20" x2="240" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="320" y1="20" x2="320" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="400" y1="20" x2="400" y2="420"/>
              </g>

              <!-- Outermost ring (faintest, dashed) -->
              <circle cx="240" cy="220" r="175" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.12" stroke-dasharray="2 4"/>

              <!-- Outer ring -->
              <circle cx="240" cy="220" r="135" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.25" opacity="0.22"/>

              <!-- Middle ring -->
              <circle cx="240" cy="220" r="92" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.4"/>

              <!-- Inner ring (orange, the inner circle) -->
              <circle cx="240" cy="220" r="50" fill="none" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="2.5"/>

              <!-- Center anchor: layered orange/navy/orange bullseye -->
              <circle cx="240" cy="220" r="28" fill="#E13D0F"/>
              <circle cx="240" cy="220" r="14" fill="#02101D"/>
              <circle cx="240" cy="220" r="5" fill="#E13D0F"/>

              <!-- Inner ring nodes (4 customers, closest access, solid orange) -->
              <circle cx="290" cy="220" r="5" fill="#E13D0F"/>
              <circle cx="240" cy="170" r="5" fill="#E13D0F"/>
              <circle cx="190" cy="220" r="5" fill="#E13D0F"/>
              <circle cx="240" cy="270" r="5" fill="#E13D0F"/>

              <!-- Middle ring nodes (6 customers, cream filled) -->
              <circle cx="332" cy="220" r="4.5" fill="#F4EFE5" opacity="0.85"/>
              <circle cx="286" cy="140" r="4.5" fill="#F4EFE5" opacity="0.85"/>
              <circle cx="194" cy="140" r="4.5" fill="#F4EFE5" opacity="0.85"/>
              <circle cx="148" cy="220" r="4.5" fill="#F4EFE5" opacity="0.85"/>
              <circle cx="194" cy="300" r="4.5" fill="#F4EFE5" opacity="0.85"/>
              <circle cx="286" cy="300" r="4.5" fill="#F4EFE5" opacity="0.85"/>

              <!-- Outer ring nodes (8 customers, cream outline only, lower opacity) -->
              <circle cx="375" cy="220" r="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.55"/>
              <circle cx="335" cy="135" r="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.55"/>
              <circle cx="240" cy="85" r="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.55"/>
              <circle cx="145" cy="135" r="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.55"/>
              <circle cx="105" cy="220" r="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.55"/>
              <circle cx="145" cy="305" r="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.55"/>
              <circle cx="240" cy="355" r="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.55"/>
              <circle cx="335" cy="305" r="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.55"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="mt-20 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 pt-10 border-t border-cream/15 relative z-10">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Role</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Sr. Director, Product Experience</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Duration</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Pilot to global rollout</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Partners</p>
          <p class="text-cream">PX, CX, Product, GTM</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">2026 Target</p>
          <p class="text-cream">4 regions, ~15% roadmap input</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- The problem statement -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="grid-backdrop border-b border-ink/10 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-top"></div>
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-bottom"></div>
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32 relative z-10">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The problem</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[28ch] mb-12">
        Customer feedback existed. A feedback system did not.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 max-w-5xl">
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          Signals came in through support tickets, sales calls, executive
          meetings, roadmap discussions, one-off customer requests, and
          relationships with assigned PMs. The signals were valuable. They
          weren't synthesized in a way that product teams could act on
          consistently.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          At the same time, Branch was entering a major product transformation
          across modernization, AI, analytics, and customer migration. Customers
          needed more than a feedback collection mechanism. They needed a way to
          feel close to the direction Branch was heading, not surprised by it.
          The work needed a customer trust and adoption mechanism, not just a
          listening one.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- THREE-PILLAR APPROACH -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The approach</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[28ch] mb-16">
      From customer event to customer infrastructure.
    </h2>

    <div class="pillar-grid">

      <!-- Reframe -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Reframe / mirror shift -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <rect x="14" y="14" width="24" height="52" fill="#02101D"/>
            <rect x="42" y="14" width="24" height="52" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            <path d="M30 36 L 22 40 L 30 44" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <path d="M50 36 L 58 40 L 50 44" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <line x1="34" y1="40" x2="46" y2="40" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Reframe</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            Program, not event.
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            The first strategic shift was treating the program as more than a
            customer gathering. A great event focuses on attendance and
            satisfaction. A great program builds a durable system for customer
            education, roadmap visibility, product feedback, executive listening,
            adoption support, and product trust.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Strategy connection -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Connection / linked nodes -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <circle cx="20" cy="20" r="8" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            <circle cx="60" cy="20" r="8" fill="#02101D"/>
            <circle cx="20" cy="60" r="8" fill="#02101D"/>
            <circle cx="60" cy="60" r="8" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="10" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
            <line x1="28" y1="28" x2="32" y2="32" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
            <line x1="52" y1="28" x2="48" y2="32" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
            <line x1="28" y1="52" x2="32" y2="48" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
            <line x1="52" y1="52" x2="48" y2="48" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow-voice mb-3">Strategy connection</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            Anchored to a North Star, not orphaned.
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            The program was placed inside the broader PX strategy: make the
            product easier to understand, easier to adopt, and harder to leave.
            Strategic placement matters. Programs that live inside a strategy get
            funded, owned, and improved. Orphaned initiatives quietly disappear.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline">
          <p class="font-display text-2xl italic text-orange">"Programs need a strategic home."</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Repeatable loop -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Loop / cycle -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path d="M40 14 a26 26 0 1 1 -26 26" fill="none" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="6" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M40 14 L 30 8 L 30 20 Z" fill="#E13D0F"/>
            <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="8" fill="#02101D"/>
            <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="3" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Repeatable loop</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            Capture, synthesize, route, return.
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            The most important operational work was designing the feedback loop
            itself. Conversations had to become themes. Themes had to be routed
            to product owners. Decisions had to be documented. Customers had to
            see something come back. The common trap of customer programs is
            great conversations that change nothing.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline"></div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- The VOC loop (visual diagram) -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="bg-cream-warm/40 border-y border-ink/10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The feedback loop</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[28ch] mb-16">
        How a conversation becomes a product decision.
      </h2>

      <!-- 6-step horizontal flow -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-6 gap-4 md:gap-6 mb-12">
        {[
          { num: '01', name: 'Conversation', desc: 'Customer feedback captured in structured settings.', color: '#E13D0F' },
          { num: '02', name: 'Theme capture', desc: 'Quotes, patterns, and asks documented.', color: '#9B40C4' },
          { num: '03', name: 'Synthesis', desc: 'Themes clustered and prioritized across customers.', color: '#062E5C' },
          { num: '04', name: 'Ownership', desc: 'Routed to the right PM, PX lead, or CX owner.', color: '#7A6A4F' },
          { num: '05', name: 'Decision', desc: 'Roadmap, education, or adoption implication named.', color: '#E13D0F' },
          { num: '06', name: 'Return', desc: 'Customer sees what happened with their input.', color: '#9B40C4' },
        ].map((step) => (
          <div class="relative p-5 md:p-6 bg-cream border border-ink/10 h-full flex flex-col" style="border-radius: 14px;">
            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0" style={`width: 5px; background: ${step.color}; border-radius: 14px 0 0 14px;`}></div>
            <div class="pl-3">
              <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-2" style={`color: ${step.color};`}>{step.num}</p>
              <p class="font-display text-lg text-ink mb-2 leading-tight">{step.name}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">{step.desc}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-reading">
        <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          The loop matters. Without explicit routing and a feedback-to-customer
          step, the program becomes extractive. With both, the program builds
          trust each time it runs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- The loop in practice: one journey through all six steps, visualized -->
      <div class="mt-20 md:mt-24">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The loop in practice</p>
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-ink leading-tight max-w-[42ch] mb-10">
          One conversation through six stations.
        </h3>

        <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed max-w-reading mb-16">
          Process diagrams describe what is supposed to happen. The test of the model is
          whether a single customer comment can travel from the conversation it started in
          to a roadmap decision and back to the customer who raised it. Here is one journey,
          anonymized.
        </p>

        <!-- The closed loop SVG -->
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 900 560" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-full h-auto" role="img" aria-label="A closed feedback loop showing one customer journey. A quote enters at the top and travels clockwise through six numbered stations around a circular loop: Conversation, Theme, Synthesis, Ownership, Decision, Return. The customer sits at the center of the loop as the destination of all activity.">

            <!-- The customer's voice, positioned above the loop -->
            <foreignObject x="180" y="30" width="540" height="60">
              <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="font-family: 'new-spirit', Georgia, serif; font-style: italic; font-size: 20px; color: #02101D; margin: 0; line-height: 1.4; text-align: center; opacity: 0.88;">"We can't get data out of the platform fast enough&nbsp;to&nbsp;act&nbsp;on&nbsp;it."</p>
            </foreignObject>

            <!-- Subtle entry line from quote down to station 01 -->
            <line x1="450" y1="100" x2="450" y2="140" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.4"/>

            <!-- The loop arc -->
            <circle cx="450" cy="330" r="170" fill="none" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.5"/>

            <!-- Center: customer (focal point) -->
            <g>
              <circle cx="450" cy="330" r="60" fill="#02101D"/>
              <text x="450" y="328" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="10" fill="#E13D0F" letter-spacing="2.5">CUSTOMER</text>
              <text x="450" y="348" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'new-spirit', Georgia, serif" font-style="italic" font-size="11" fill="#F4EFE5" opacity="0.65">at the center</text>
            </g>

            <!-- Station 01: Conversation (top, emphasized) -->
            <g>
              <circle cx="450" cy="160" r="30" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <text x="450" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="13" fill="#E13D0F" letter-spacing="1.5" font-weight="500">01</text>
            </g>

            <!-- Station 02: Theme (2 o'clock) -->
            <g>
              <circle cx="597" cy="245" r="26" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#9B40C4" stroke-width="2"/>
              <text x="597" y="251" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="12" fill="#9B40C4" letter-spacing="1.5" font-weight="500">02</text>
            </g>

            <!-- Station 03: Synthesis (4 o'clock) -->
            <g>
              <circle cx="597" cy="415" r="26" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#062E5C" stroke-width="2"/>
              <text x="597" y="421" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="12" fill="#062E5C" letter-spacing="1.5" font-weight="500">03</text>
            </g>

            <!-- Station 04: Ownership (bottom) -->
            <g>
              <circle cx="450" cy="500" r="26" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#7A6A4F" stroke-width="2"/>
              <text x="450" y="506" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="12" fill="#7A6A4F" letter-spacing="1.5" font-weight="500">04</text>
            </g>

            <!-- Station 05: Decision (8 o'clock, emphasized) -->
            <g>
              <circle cx="303" cy="415" r="30" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <text x="303" y="421" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="13" fill="#E13D0F" letter-spacing="1.5" font-weight="500">05</text>
            </g>

            <!-- Station 06: Return (10 o'clock) -->
            <g>
              <circle cx="303" cy="245" r="26" fill="#FFFFFF" stroke="#9B40C4" stroke-width="2"/>
              <text x="303" y="251" text-anchor="middle" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="12" fill="#9B40C4" letter-spacing="1.5" font-weight="500">06</text>
            </g>

          </svg>

          <!-- Caption strip below the image: the key to reading the visual -->
          <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-6 gap-6 md:gap-4 pt-8 border-t border-ink/8">
            <div class="text-left md:text-center">
              <p class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] font-semibold mb-1.5" style="color: #E13D0F;">01</p>
              <p class="font-display text-sm text-ink mb-1 leading-tight">Conversation</p>
              <p class="font-display text-xs text-ink-soft italic leading-snug">London cohort</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-left md:text-center">
              <p class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] font-semibold mb-1.5" style="color: #9B40C4;">02</p>
              <p class="font-display text-sm text-ink mb-1 leading-tight">Theme</p>
              <p class="font-display text-xs text-ink-soft italic leading-snug">Export velocity</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-left md:text-center">
              <p class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] font-semibold mb-1.5" style="color: #062E5C;">03</p>
              <p class="font-display text-sm text-ink mb-1 leading-tight">Synthesis</p>
              <p class="font-display text-xs text-ink-soft italic leading-snug">6 customers</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-left md:text-center">
              <p class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] font-semibold mb-1.5" style="color: #7A6A4F;">04</p>
              <p class="font-display text-sm text-ink mb-1 leading-tight">Ownership</p>
              <p class="font-display text-xs text-ink-soft italic leading-snug">Data platform PM</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-left md:text-center">
              <p class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] font-semibold mb-1.5" style="color: #E13D0F;">05</p>
              <p class="font-display text-sm text-ink mb-1 leading-tight">Decision</p>
              <p class="font-display text-xs text-ink-soft italic leading-snug">P1 next quarter</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-left md:text-center">
              <p class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.15em] font-semibold mb-1.5" style="color: #9B40C4;">06</p>
              <p class="font-display text-sm text-ink mb-1 leading-tight">Return</p>
              <p class="font-display text-xs text-ink-soft italic leading-snug">Customer hears back</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Closing serif line -->
          <p class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-ink text-center leading-snug mt-14 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            One conversation. Six stations. One roadmap commitment in a single&nbsp;planning&nbsp;cycle.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-16 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-ink-muted text-center max-w-reading mx-auto">
          Anonymized example. The mechanism, not the exact customer or product detail.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- Regional rollout -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The rollout</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[28ch] mb-16">
      Pilot first. Expand intentionally.
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <!-- Step 1: EMEA pilot -->
      <div class="lesson-card">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="linocut-icon mb-3">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="28" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
                <path d="M14 40 Q 26 28, 40 30 Q 54 32, 66 40" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
                <path d="M14 40 Q 26 52, 40 50 Q 54 48, 66 40" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
                <ellipse cx="40" cy="40" rx="10" ry="28" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
                <line x1="40" y1="12" x2="40" y2="68" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2"/>
                <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="eyebrow mb-2">Phase 01</p>
            <p class="font-display text-2xl text-ink leading-tight">EMEA pilot.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mt-2">London</p>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-4">
              The first program launched in London as a regional pilot. The
              format was intimate: a small group of customers, roadmap
              visibility, AI and product demos, structured conversation, and
              real time for feedback. Charcuterie included.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              The pilot validated customer appetite for closer engagement with
              Branch's product direction, surfaced which formats customers
              valued most (roadmap visibility and AI demos outperformed feature
              voting), and proved the model could produce structured product
              signal, not just qualitative reception.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 2: NA rollout -->
      <div class="lesson-card">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="linocut-icon mb-3">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="28" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
                <path d="M14 40 Q 22 26, 30 32 Q 38 38, 32 50 Q 26 60, 38 64 Q 50 68, 54 56 Q 58 44, 50 38 Q 42 32, 50 22 Q 56 14, 64 24" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <circle cx="30" cy="34" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
                <circle cx="50" cy="44" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
                <circle cx="44" cy="58" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="eyebrow-voice mb-2">Phase 02</p>
            <p class="font-display text-2xl text-ink leading-tight">North America rollout.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mt-2">CX-led roadshow</p>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-4">
              The North America expansion required cross-functional enablement.
              CX partners needed to understand the program, speak about it
              confidently, and help bring the right customers into the right
              conversations. The VP of Customer Experience advocated for the
              program internally and championed cross-functional ownership.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              The rollout shifted the program from "Product Experience
              initiative" to "company-wide customer engagement system,"
              strengthening its position as part of the broader product
              transformation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 3: Formalization -->
      <div class="lesson-card">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="linocut-icon mb-3">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <rect x="14" y="14" width="52" height="52" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
                <line x1="14" y1="40" x2="66" y2="40" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="40" y1="14" x2="40" y2="66" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <circle cx="27" cy="27" r="4" fill="#02101D"/>
                <circle cx="53" cy="27" r="4" fill="#02101D"/>
                <circle cx="27" cy="53" r="4" fill="#02101D"/>
                <circle cx="53" cy="53" r="4" fill="#02101D"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="eyebrow mb-2">Phase 03</p>
            <p class="font-display text-2xl text-ink leading-tight">Formalization.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mt-2">Strategic placement</p>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-4">
              The program was formalized as part of the Product Experience
              strategy. It connected directly to the Product Mastery & Community
              pillar, joining customer education, advisory programs, and
              community-led learning under one strategic identity.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              Formalization is what turns a successful pilot into durable
              infrastructure. Without it, programs survive at the pace of
              individual champion energy. With it, the program survives
              leadership transitions, funding cycles, and reorgs.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

